&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:aptos,aptos_embeddedfont,aptos_msfontservice,sans-serif; font-size:12pt"&gt;(Vancouver, WA) -- This past weekend, more than 400 students and faculty from Pacific Northwest, predominantly undergraduate institutions gathered to present and celebrate science research at the 34&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:aptos,aptos_embeddedfont,aptos_msfontservice,sans-serif; font-size:9.5pt"&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:aptos,aptos_embeddedfont,aptos_msfontservice,sans-serif; font-size:12pt"&gt; annual Murdock College Science Research (MCSR) Conference. Hosted by the M.J. Murdock Charitable Trust, the conference focused on sharing and advancing new knowledge and celebrating student and faculty research.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:aptos,aptos_embeddedfont,aptos_msfontservice,sans-serif; font-size:12pt"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

